<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-03T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-03T04:00:00-05:00" n="169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11048: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-03T17:00:00+08:00">August 3, 1930—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 3—11:15 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>661. Legations 649, August 1, 6 p.m. Following from American Consul at
                            Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>August 3, 3 p.m. Communists still hold Changsha although main
                                    body has apparently moved east toward Liuyang.</p>
                                <p>Very strict martial law in Wuhan, all traffic prohibited midnight
                                    to dawn.</p>
                                <p>Foreign naval vessels in Hankow: British, one gunboat; French,
                                        <pb facs="0259" n="161" xml:id="pg_161"/> three gunboats;
                                    Japanese, one cruiser, three gunboats; American, one gunboat.
                                    Italian gunboat will arrive tomorrow.</p>
                                <p>On July 31st, through <hi rend="italic">Monocacy</hi> at
                                    Kiukiang, I warned Americans to withdraw from Kuling at
                                    once.</p>
                                <p>Jordan,<note n="72" xml:id="d169fn72">Russell B. Jordan, Vice
                                        Consul at Hankow.</note> who resigned effective August 3,
                                    will remain for a week or 10 days at Nanking.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>